  "result_text": "The short circuit analysis on the **7-bus system** at the **S/E A 13.8 kV** bus has been completed using the **Complete method** (which provides a full network voltage and current profile).\n\n### Analysis Summary\n- **Target Bus:** S/E A 13.8 kV\n- **Fault Type:** Single-phase-to-ground (SPGF)\n- **Standard:** IEC 60909 (calculated via Complete method for profile extraction)\n- **Status:** Success\n\n### Fault Currents at S/E A 13.8 kV\n| Parameter | Symbol | Value | Unit |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| Initial Symmetrical SC Current | $I''_{k}$ | **40.00** | kA |\n| Peak SC Current | $i_{p}$ | **98.77** | kA |\n| Steady-state SC Current | $I_{k}$ | **40.00** | kA |\n| Short-circuit Power | $S''_{k}$ | **956.09** | MVA |\n\n### Network Impact\nThe analysis reveals that the fault at this specific bus causes a **total voltage collapse (0.0 pu)** across all monitored buses in the system. This occurs because the primary (and in this configuration, only active) source, \"**Red Externa**\" (External Grid), is connected directly to the faulted bus. Consequently, the entire current flows directly into the fault, and the rest of the network, being downstream of the fault and lacking additional sources, drops to zero voltage.\n\n### Branch Contributions\n| Element | Side | Current (kA) |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Red Externa** | Connection | 40.00 |\n| Other Branches | - | 0.00 |\n\n*Note: The 40 kA value is the defined fault contribution of the \"Red Externa\" element at this location.*\n\n### Timing & Performance\n- **Project Load:** 31.28 s\n- **Calculation Execution:** 1.61 s\n- **Total Process Time:** 32.90 s\n\nDetailed results have been saved to `results/sc_final_results.json`.",
